Using min method:

n=int(input("Enter total numbers:"))
nums=[]
for i in range(n):
    num=int(input("Enter a number:"))
    nums.append(num)
print("Largest number:",min(nums))

Without using min method:

n=int(input("Enter total numbers:"))
small=int(input("Enter number:"))
for i in range(n-1):
    num=int(input("Enter a number:"))
    if num<small:
        small=num
print("The smallest number is:",small)
